    <header>
        <h1>Nigel Thomas</h1>
        <p>Hospitality Professional | 20+ Years at Sea • USA • Middle East • India</p>
    </header>

    <div class="bio-content">

        <h2>🇮🇳 Early Life & Education</h2>
        <p><strong>Born in Bangalore on January 27, 1952</strong>. I grew up in the Garden City and completed my schooling at <strong>St. Joseph's Indian High School</strong>, one of Bangalore's most respected institutions. Those formative years taught me discipline, resilience, and the value of hard work — lessons that would guide my entire career.</p>

        <h2>🇮🇳 The Beginning – Mumbai & Rahat Palace</h2>
        <p>After completing my education, I migrated to Mumbai, the city of dreams. I started my hospitality career at <strong>Rahat Palace, Worli, Mumbai</strong>. This is where I learned the basics of hotel operations, guest service, and working under pressure. Mumbai's fast-paced environment prepared me for the international stage.</p>

        <h2>🇦🇪🇮🇶 Middle East Years – Ramada, Meridien, and Baghdad</h2>
        <p>My journey then took me to the Middle East. I worked at the <strong>Ramada Hotel</strong> and <strong>Meridien Hotel</strong>, where I was exposed to international standards of luxury service. I also spent time in <strong>Baghdad, Iraq</strong>, at the <strong>Al Hambra Hotel</strong>, which was a unique and challenging experience. In total, I spent about <strong>6 years in the Middle East</strong>, learning to manage diverse teams and adapt to different cultural expectations.</p>

        <h2>🇺🇸 Twenty+ Years at Sea – US Cruise Ships</h2>
        <p>My most significant professional chapter began when I joined <strong>US cruise ships</strong>. For <strong>over 20 years</strong>, I sailed across the Caribbean, Bahamas, and US coasts, managing multi-outlet F&B operations for premium brands. I led teams of <strong>100+ crew members</strong>, oversaw revenues exceeding <strong>$250,000 per voyage</strong>, and acted as project leader for dry dock refurbishments and new builds. Life at sea taught me operational excellence, crisis management, and how to deliver consistent quality in a moving, multicultural environment.</p>

        <h2>🇺🇸 On Land in the USA</h2>
        <p>After my sea career, I spent several years working on land in the United States as a <strong>Restaurant Operations Manager</strong>, directing high-volume locations from pre-opening to full maturity. This phase deepened my understanding of American-style service, cost control, and team leadership.</p>

        <h2>🇮🇳 Returning to India – Bangalore, Hyderabad & Nandi Hills</h2>
        <p>After decades abroad, I returned to India. I have worked across <strong>Bangalore, Hyderabad, and Nandi Hills</strong>, bringing my global experience to the growing Indian hospitality sector. Whether it is a fast-paced corporate hotel in Bangalore, a culturally rich property in Hyderabad, or a serene nature-focused resort in Nandi Hills, I have adapted and thrived. My focus remains on operational efficiency, team building, and guest satisfaction.</p>

        <h3>🌍 Total International Experience</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>20+ years</strong> on US cruise ships (Caribbean, Bahamas, US coasts)</li>
            <li><strong>6 years</strong> in the Middle East (UAE, Iraq)</li>
            <li><strong>Several years</strong> on land in the USA</li>
            <li><strong>5+ years</strong> in India (Bangalore, Hyderabad, Nandi Hills)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>💡 What I Bring to Every Team</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Hands-on operations management across three continents and at sea</li>
            <li>Deep understanding of food & beverage, banquets, and guest relations</li>
            <li>Team training and leadership – I build people who build businesses</li>
            <li>Crisis management – from kitchen fires to VIP guest escalations</li>
            <li>Cost control and inventory management – proven track record of 12-15% improvement</li>
            <li>AI-powered operations and automation (certified 2024)</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>My philosophy is simple:</strong> Respect the craft, respect your team, and never stop learning. Whether it is a 5 AM airport pickup for a VIP or a last-minute banquet for 500 guests, I get it done. From Bangalore to Baghdad, from Mumbai to Miami, I have served with integrity and pride.</p>

